# No rules on purpose. Cloudflare Pages already serves /about, /products,
# /service-areas, and /contact from their matching .html files natively —
# no rewrite needed. A `/* /index.html 200` fallback (or any rule whose
# target is a bare `name.html`) loops on Cloudflare Pages: it rewrites the
# request, then Cloudflare's own .html-extension-strip redirect sends the
# browser back to the same clean path, which re-matches the rule forever.
# Confirmed live: /about with a `/about /about.html 200` rule 308-looped.
# Unmatched paths correctly fall through to Cloudflare's default 404.
